---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Tech Interview Prep by Company | What to Expect at Top Employers"
description: "Prepare for tech interviews at visa-sponsoring companies. Learn about interview processes, rounds, tech stacks, and tips for Zalando, Spotify, Revolut, and more."
---

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Tech Interview Prep by Company",
      "url": "{{ site.url }}/tools/interview-prep/",
      "description": "{{ description }}",
      "applicationCategory": "EducationalApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "Any",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "EUR" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" }
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How many interview rounds do top tech companies have?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Most top visa-sponsoring tech companies have 3-5 interview rounds. This typically includes a recruiter screen, one or two technical interviews (coding and/or system design), and a team fit or culture interview. Companies like Revolut may have 5 rounds, while Bolt and Form3 often complete the process in 3 rounds."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How long does the interview process take at visa-sponsoring companies?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The interview timeline typically ranges from 2-5 weeks. Fast companies like Bolt and Wise can complete the process in 2-3 weeks. Spotify and Datadog may take 3-5 weeks. The visa sponsorship process adds additional time after you receive an offer, typically 2-8 weeks depending on the country."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What should I prepare for a system design interview?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "For system design interviews, practice designing scalable distributed systems. Focus on: load balancing, database sharding, caching strategies, message queues, and microservices architecture. For e-commerce companies (Zalando, Booking.com), prepare for high-traffic scenarios. For fintech (Revolut, Adyen), focus on consistency and reliability in financial systems."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do I need to mention visa sponsorship during interviews?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "You should be transparent about your visa requirements early in the process, ideally during the recruiter screen. All companies listed on VisaJobs.xyz already sponsor visas, so this won't disqualify you. Being upfront helps both parties plan the timeline and avoids surprises later in the process."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-white to-violet-50 dark:from-gray-950 dark:via-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400">Home</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Tools</span>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Interview Prep</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-violet-100 dark:bg-violet-900/30 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center">
        <i data-lucide="message-square-code" class="w-7 h-7 text-violet-600 dark:text-violet-400"></i>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Interview Prep by Company</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Know what to expect before you apply</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mb-8">
      Get insider knowledge on interview processes at top visa-sponsoring companies. Learn the number of rounds, tech stacks, timelines, and tips to ace your interviews.
    </p>
    <div class="max-w-xl">
      <div class="relative">
        <i data-lucide="search" class="w-5 h-5 absolute left-4 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-gray-400"></i>
        <input type="text" id="company-search" class="input-field w-full pl-12 pr-4 py-3" placeholder="Search for a company (e.g., Spotify, Zalando, Revolut)..." autocomplete="off">
      </div>
      <div id="search-suggestions" class="hidden absolute z-20 w-full max-w-xl mt-1 bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Selected company detail #}
<section id="company-detail" class="py-12 hidden">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div id="company-card" class="card p-6 md:p-8"></div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Server-rendered grid for SEO #}
<section class="py-12">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4">
    <h2 class="section-heading mb-8">All Companies with Interview Guides</h2>
    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4" id="company-grid">
      {% for company in companies %}
      <div class="card p-5 hover:border-brand-300 dark:hover:border-brand-600 transition-colors cursor-pointer company-grid-item" data-slug="{{ company.slug }}">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <img src="/media/{{ company.slug }}_logo.jpg" alt="{{ company.name }}" class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg object-cover" loading="lazy" onerror="this.src='/favicon/android-chrome-192x192.png'">
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">{{ company.name }}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">{{ company.hq }}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-3">{{ company.industry }}</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <span class="badge">{{ company.size }} employees</span>
          {% if company.relocation %}<span class="badge" style="background:rgb(220 252 231);color:rgb(22 101 52)"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-3 h-3 inline mr-1"></i>Relocation</span>{% endif %}
        </div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

